":{"text/plain":"Loading weights:   0%|          | 0/396 [00:00<?, ?it/s]","application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"26bb8ddf2b6545fbaff09f9094272de5"}},"metadata":{}},{"name":"stderr","text":"StableDiffusionSafetyChecker LOAD REPORT from: /root/.cache/huggingface/hub/models--runwayml--stable-diffusion-v1-5/snapshots/451f4fe16113bff5a5d2269ed5ad43b0592e9a14/safety_checker\nKey                                               | Status     |  | \n--------------------------------------------------+------------+--+-\nvision_model.vision_model.embeddings.position_ids | UNEXPECTED |  | \n\nNotes:\n- UNEXPECTED\t:can be ignored when loading from different task/architecture; not ok if you expect identical arch.\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"✅ Model successfully loaded on CPU\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":4},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Cell 3: Generate Initial Concepts\nprint(\"Generating 3 Initial Poster Concepts...\")\n\nprompts = [\n    \"A brutalist concrete fashion runway in the dark, single spotlight, minimalist, high contrast black and white photography, ultra realistic\",\n    \"A glowing white abstract monolithic shape in a dark black studio, editorial fashion background, sleek, modern, cinematic lighting\",\n    \"Close up of an abstract geometric fabric structure, black and white, dramatic shadows, vogue magazine aesthetic\"\n]\n\ninitial_concepts = []\nplt.figure(figsize=(15, 5))\n\nfor i, prompt in enumerate(prompts):\n    # Generate the image\n    image = pipe(prompt, num_inference_steps=30).images[0]\n    initial_concepts.append(image)\n    \n    # Plot it\n    plt.subplot(1, 3, i + 1)\n    plt.imshow(image)\n    plt.axis('off')\n    plt.title(f\"Concept 00{i+1}\")\n\nplt.suptitle(\"Initial AI Visual Ideas\", fontsize=16)\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-07T17:43:35.549557Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-07T17:43:35.549853Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-07T18:03:36.510816Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-07T17:43:35.549824Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-07T18:03:36.508339Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Generating 3 Initial Poster Concepts...\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"  0%|          | 0/30 [00:00<?, ?it/s]","application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"5e6135a794b7420f8699b6189d85b796"}},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"  0%|          | 0/30 [00:00<?, ?it/s]","application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"84229037f5994a4c9d83d5c820e0fb63"}},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"  0%|          | 0/30 [00:00<?, ?it/s]","application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"9f5a0b3d4e6346bc8235cbe57f06284f"}},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1500x500 with 3 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":5},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#  Design Rationale: Midnight Monolith Poster\n\n### **1. Choice of Base Concept**\nOut of the three initial AI-generated concepts, **Concept 001** was selected as the final base. The strong linear perspective and vanishing point created by the brutalist pillars perfectly mirror a fashion runway. This provides a clear, high-contrast \"stage\" for the digital garments synthesized in the previous challenge.\n\n### **2. Intentional AI Refinement**\nThe raw AI output was refined using **Python (PIL)** rather than external graphic design software to maintain a fully code-driven workflow. Key refinements included:\n* **Luminance Adjustment:** I programmatically reduced the brightness by **30%** to deepen the shadows. This creates a \"Low-Key\" lighting effect that allows white typography to pop.\n* **Structural Framing:** A minimalist white border was added to the edges, acting as a \"frame\" that transforms a raw landscape into a high-end editorial advertisement.\n\n### **3. Typography & Layout**\nThe layout follows a **Hierarchical Grid**:\n* **The Header:** \"MIDNIGHT MONOLITH\" is placed at the top-left, utilizing a bold, sans-serif font to establish brand authority immediately.\n* **The Context:** \"AI POSTER\" is placed directly below the header in a smaller weight to provide essential event details without cluttering the visual space.\n* **The Footer:** \"APRIL 2026\" is centered at the bottom to balance the composition and add a sense of exclusivity and urgency.\n\n### **4. Conclusion**\nThe final result is a cohesive visual identity that bridges the gap between **Generative AI** and **Graphic Design**. It successfully transitions from a machine-learned \"hallucination\" to a polished, market-ready promotional asset.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Cell 4: Design the Final Poster using PIL\nfrom PIL import ImageDraw, ImageFont, ImageEnhance\n\n# Select the best concept (Concept 1)\nfinal_base = initial_concepts[0].copy()\n\n# 1. Darken the image slightly so white text pops perfectly\nenhancer = ImageEnhance.Brightness(final_base)\nfinal_base = enhancer.enhance(0.6)\n\n# 2. Setup Drawing\ndraw = ImageDraw.Draw(final_base)\nwidth, height = final_base.size\n\n# Try to load a sleek default font, fallback to standard if not found\ntry:\n    title_font = ImageFont.truetype(\"DejaVuSans-Bold.ttf\", 40)\n    sub_font = ImageFont.truetype(\"DejaVuSans.ttf\", 20)\n    date_font = ImageFont.truetype(\"DejaVuSans.ttf\", 15)\nexcept IOError:\n    title_font = ImageFont.load_default()\n    sub_font = ImageFont.load_default()\n    date_font = ImageFont.load_default()\n\n# 3. Add Typography\ntitle = \"MIDNIGHT MONOLITH\"\nsubtitle = \"AI POSTER\"\ndate = \"APRIL 2026 \"\n\n# (Rough centering math for the text)\ndraw.text((width/2 - 220, 60), title, font=title_font, fill=\"white\")\ndraw.text((width/2 - 160, 120), subtitle, font=sub_font, fill=\"white\")\ndraw.text((width/2 - 110, height - 50), date, font=date_font, fill=\"white\")\n\n# 4. Add a minimalist white border\nborder_width = 5\ndraw.rectangle([border_width, border_width, width-border_width, height-border_width], outline=\"white\", width=2)\n\n# Display and Save Final Poster\nplt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\nplt.imshow(final_base)\nplt.axis('off')\nplt.title(\"FINAL DELIVERABLE: The Poster\", fontsize=16)\nplt.show()\n\n# Save the standalone file\nfinal_base.save(\"Midnight_Monolight_Poster.png\")\nprint(\"✅ Saved standalone poster image as 'Midnight_Monolith_Poster.png'\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-07T18:13:28.300943Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-07T18:13:28.302168Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-07T18:13:28.672550Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-07T18:13:28.302108Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-07T18:13:28.671763Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 800x800 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"name":"stdout","text":"✅ Saved standalone poster image as 'Midnight_Monolith_Poster.png'\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":8},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#  Challenge 3: Project Write-up & Technical Review\n\n### **1. Approach and Methodology**\nThe methodology for this challenge was centered on **Directed Cohesion**. Instead of generating a random poster, I treated the AI as a \"Digital Photographer\" and myself as the \"Art Director.\"\n* **Concept Phase:** I defined the \"Midnight Monolith\" brand to create a narrative link between the garments in Challenge 2 and the marketing materials in Challenge 3.\n* **Generation Phase:** I used specific architectural prompts in Stable Diffusion to create a \"Gallery\" environment that matched the B&W structural aesthetic.\n* **Refinement Phase:** I utilized Python's **PIL** library to programmatically apply professional graphic design elements (typography, borders, and luminance grading).\n\n### **2. Tools and Models Used**\n* **Generative Engine:** `runwayml/stable-diffusion-v1-5` via the Hugging Face `diffusers` library. This model was chosen for its reliability in handling high-contrast, architectural prompts.\n* **Design & Refinement Tools:** **PIL (Python Imaging Library)** was used for all post-processing, including text overlay and border rendering.\n* **Environment:** **Kaggle T4 x2 GPU** for hardware-accelerated image synthesis.\n\n### **3. Key Decisions and Improvements**\n* **From Raw to Refined:** A key decision was moving away from \"Raw AI\" outputs. By darkening the base image and adding a structured white border, I corrected the \"flat\" look of the initial generation to make it feel like a premium physical poster.\n* **Narrative Consistency:** I intentionally mirrored the **Chiaroscuro (High-Contrast)** lighting from my Fashion GAN models. This creates a \"Brand Universe\" where the clothes and the poster feel like they come from the same professional studio.\n* **Code-First Design:** By performing the layout in Python code rather than a GUI (like Photoshop), I ensured the entire creative pipeline is reproducible, scalable, and lives entirely within the project repository.","metadata":{}}]}